arget=\"#feedbackModal_main_2529923\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mho1665702920207.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mho1665702920207.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mho1665702920207.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mho1665702920207\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Entity-Level Declarative Constraints\n \n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mho1665702920207__entity_level_declarative_constraints_139131\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mho1665702920207__p_d45068e1_d45069e1_d45070e1\">The following declarative constraints exist at entity level:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mho1665702920207__li_d22355e1_d22356e1_d22357e1\">If compound primary or candidate keys are defined, all fields in the key must contain data (by default, incomplete keys fail validation).\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mho1665702920207__li_d22358e1_d22359e1_d22360e1\">The total number of occurrences in the entity must be between the minimum and maximum specified in the entity properties. By default, this constraint is not defined.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mho1665702920207__topic_d29202e1_d29203e1_d29204e1_d29205e1_d29206e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d438414e68\">\n                        \n Compound Keys Must Be Complete\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mho1665702920207__p_d45074e1_d45075e1_d45076e1\">When a compound primary or candidate key is validated, Uniface first checks if the key is complete. A complete key means that all fields belonging to that key contain data, except for fields that have a syntax definition of LEN(0-0). If the key is not complete, Uniface sets <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$error</span> to 2206 and activates the entity-level error trigger. The validation process fails, and the validateKey trigger (or any other trigger) is not activated.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mho1665702920207__topic_d29207e1_d29208e1_d29209e1_d29210e1_d29211e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d438414e80\">\n                        \n Minimum and Maximum Number of Occurrences\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mho1665702920207__p_d45080e1_d45081e1_d45082e1\">The minimum and maximum number of occurrences can be specified when defining modeled entities and component entities in the Uniface IDE. When an entity is validated, Uniface checks whether the number of occurrences is within the range of the minimum and maximum specified. If this validation check fails, Uniface sets <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$error</span> to 0102 or 0103, depending on the violated definition, and activates the entity-level error trigger. The function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$error</span> is set to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mho1665702920207__li_d22361e1_d22362e1_d22363e1\">0102 if the number of occurrences is less than the minimum\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mho1665702920207__li_d22364e1_d22365e1_d22366e1\">0103 if the number of occurrences is greater than the maximum\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"mho1665702920207__note_w4464ab1b5b9b7_w4465ab1b5b9_w4466ab1b5_w4467ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Occurrences created with ProcScript are validated before declarative validation for the entity is performed.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529923\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529923\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Entity-Level Declarative Constraints Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Entity-Level Declarative Constraints The following declarative constraints exist at entity level: If compound primary or candidate keys are defined, all fields in the key must contain data (by default, incomplete keys fail validation). The total number of occurrences in the entity must be between the minimum and maximum specified in the entity properties. By default, this constraint is not defined. Compound Keys Must Be Complete When a compound primary or candidate key is validated, Uniface first checks if the key is complete. A complete key means that all fields belonging to that key contain data, except for fields that have a syntax definition of LEN(0-0). If the key is not complete, Uniface sets $error to 2206 and activates the entity-level error trigger. The validation process fails, and the validateKey trigger (or any other trigger) is not activated. Minimum and Maximum Number of Occurrences The minimum and maximum number of occurrences can be specified when defining modeled entities and component entities in the Uniface IDE. When an entity is validated, Uniface checks whether the number of occurrences is within the range of the minimum and maximum specified. If this validation check fails, Uniface sets $error to 0102 or 0103, depending on the violated definition, and activates the entity-level error trigger. The function $error is set to: 0102 if the number of occurrences is less than the minimum 0103 if the number of occurrences is greater than the maximum Note: Occurrences created with ProcScript are validated before declarative validation for the entity is performed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}